<promed@promedmail.org>
[Most suspected cases of vCJD outside of Europe have not been confirmed,
except where the patients have resided for a period in the UK or other
parts of Europe at the height of the BSE epidemic. It is implied that the
New Zealand patient may have contracted vCJD in the UK, or another part of
Europe where BSE-infected cattle have been reported, but neither of these
two reports confirms this directly. More precise information is awaited. -
Mod.CP]
